results.lead_paragraph: The U.N. General Assembly, convening in New York last week for its seventeenth annual session, confronted an agenda of 93 items covering most of the great problems confronting the world. Though the U.N. has no power of decision that would permit it to deal fundamentally with most of the world's basic problem, it nonetheless serves as a major forum for debate --and propaganda--in the world power struggles.
